5 years 7 months ago
“Who needs acquaintances? On the homestay I had been paired with a German girl, a part of I had a grave dislike for: she was overly picky, practically prissy, and worse – she never spoke!” I’m laughing outloud! That’s the worst, when girls are really opinionated and stuck up, it makes me want to run for the hills. Thank God I’m shy and dislike socializing most of the time. But the point is that you have to develop a mindset for it as much as you can (I’ve lived in two different regions of Illinois, with Polish people and Italian people or Polish people and Indians, it hasn’t made me angry! But I’m extremely friendly, plus I exercise frequently, so I’m more of a workaholic at networking than most people. I’m not too good with entertainment either.
